<section xml:id="c3s1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>The Independence Number</title>

    <p>In many situations, one is interested in investigating subsets of vertices of a 
        graph with certain properties. The most often studied such subsets are 
        independent sets and cliques. </p>

    
    <definition xml:id="def-indset">
        <statement>
            <p>blabla
                Let <m>G=(V,E)</m> be a graph. A subset of vertices <m>I</m> of <m>G</m> is called independent
                if no two vertices in <m>I</m> are adjacent. 
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

<figure xml:id="fig1c3s1">
    <caption>A graph on 6 vertices</caption>
<image width="60%">
  <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org"
             label="prefigure-ex1c3s1">
