    <remark>
        <p>In the graph in <xref ref="fig1c3s1"/>, the sets <m>\{1\}</m>, <m>\{1,5\}</m> and <m>\{2,4,6\}</m> are independent.</p>
    </remark>

     <remark>
        <p>In the graph in <xref ref="fig1c3s1"/>, the sets <m>\{1,2\}</m> and <m>\{3,4,6\}</m> are not independent.</p>
    </remark>


   


    <definition xml:id="def-clique">
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>G=(V,E)</m> be a graph. A subset of vertices <m>K</m> of <m>G</m> is called a clique
                if any two vertices in <m>K</m> are adjacent. 
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

<p>In the graph in <xref ref="fig1c3s1"/>, the sets <m>\{1,4\}</m> and <m>\{1,2,3\}</m> are cliques while the sets 
<m>\{1,2,3,4\} </m> is not a clique.
</p>

 <definition xml:id="def-cliquenumber">
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>G=(V,E)</m> be a graph. The clique number <m>\omega(G)</m> of <m>G</m>
                is the maximum size of an clique of <m>G</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>


